  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool <em>stineb/rpmodel</em> by Benjamin Stocker, associated with ETH Zurich, has seen a noteworthy engagement, with over 1,101 views and 222 downloads on Zenodo, indicating an active interest and potential utility in the research community.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The software tool <em>stineb/rpmodel</em>, contributed by Benjamin Stocker from ETH Zurich and available on Zenodo, serves as a significant addition to the field of computational modeling. With 1,101 views and 222 downloads, the engagement metrics reflect a strong interest and highlight its potential value for researchers looking to employ advanced modeling techniques.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">As a resource, this software supports various applications in computational sciences, emphasizing the growing trend towards structured and accessible research outputs. The availability of this tool on Zenodo underscores a commitment to make scientific resources openly accessible, thereby fostering collaboration and enabling reproducibility within the research community.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citation metrics or community discussions on platforms like Wikipedia or Reddit, the number of views and downloads signals a positive reception among peer researchers and indicates potential for future citations as the software tool is utilized in academic projects. This pattern of engagement provides a foundation for expected downstream use in various research endeavors.</p>\n\n<p class=\"story-text\">The release of <em>stineb/rpmodel</em> aligns with broader movements towards transparency and open data practices in science, reflecting an institutional commitment from ETH Zurich to advance knowledge sharing. Overall, the initial response to this software tool suggests it has the potential to contribute significant insights to computational modeling methodologies in the future.</p>",
